# Solar Sanchalak Website Specification

## Objective

Build a professional SaaS landing page for **Solar Sanchalak**, a software platform currently under development by Nogginhaus Energy.

The page serves three audiences:

Primary:
- investors
- cloud credit programs (Google Cloud, accelerators)

Secondary:
- early pilot customers
- EPC companies evaluating the platform

The website should communicate that:

- the product solves a real operational problem
- the system architecture exists
- the platform is actively being developed
- the founder has a clear long-term vision

The tone should be credible and professional, similar to early-stage SaaS companies such as Stripe, Linear, or Notion.

---

# Website Structure

The website should consist of **one primary product page**.

Optional additional pages may include:

- About
- Contact

But the product story should live on a single page.

Page layout:

Hero  
Problem  
Solution  
Product Capabilities  
How It Works  
Technology Architecture  
Development Progress  
Vision  
Call to Action

---

# Section 1 — Hero

Title

Solar Sanchalak

Subtitle

Digitizing solar inspection and maintenance workflows.

Description

Solar Sanchalak is a mobile-first platform designed for solar EPC and operations teams to digitize inspection workflows, capture field data, generate signed reports, and maintain structured maintenance records across multiple solar sites.

Primary button

