---

# Section 2 — The Problem

Title

Solar maintenance is still largely manual.

Content

Many solar EPC and operations teams still rely on paper inspection checklists, manual report preparation, and fragmented messaging tools to manage maintenance operations.

This leads to:

- inconsistent inspection records
- delayed issue reporting
- inefficient field coordination
- lack of centralized visibility across solar sites

As solar infrastructure grows, these manual processes become difficult to scale.

---

# Section 3 — The Solution

Title

A structured platform for solar maintenance operations.

Content

Solar Sanchalak provides a mobile-first platform for technicians and supervisors to manage inspection workflows and maintain centralized maintenance records.

The platform enables organizations to:

- standardize inspection procedures
- capture structured maintenance data
- collect field photos of equipment
- digitally sign inspection reports
- generate automated PDF documentation
- notify supervisors of completed inspections

The result is a centralized and searchable maintenance history for solar assets.

---

# Section 4 — Product Capabilities

Title

Core Platform Capabilities

Feature cards should include:

Multi-Tenant Organization Management  
Companies can manage multiple solar sites within one system.

User and Role Management  
Supervisors and technicians have defined access and responsibilities.

Site and Asset Registration  
Solar plants and equipment can be tracked within the platform.

Inspection Workflows  
Technicians perform structured inspections through the mobile app.

Photo Capture  
Equipment issues can be documented with images during inspections.

Digital Signatures  
Inspection reports can be digitally signed by technicians.

Automated PDF Reports  
Inspection reports are generated automatically after completion.

Supervisor Notifications  
Supervisors receive alerts when inspections are completed.

Cloud-Based Inspection History  
All inspection records are stored securely in the cloud.

---

# Section 5 — How the Platform Works

Title

How Solar Sanchalak Works

Step 1  
Organizations register their solar sites and equipment.

Step 2  
Technicians perform inspections using the mobile application.

Step 3  
Photos, inspection data, and technician signatures are captured digitally.

Step 4  
Inspection reports are generated automatically as PDF documents.

Step 5  
Supervisors receive notifications and maintain centralized maintenance records.

